    "plan_content": "Here's my complete implementation plan for the Ollama model rename feature:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n**4 files to modify, ~80 lines of new code, no new imports needed anywhere.**\n\n### Step 1 — `api/types.go`: Add `RenameRequest` struct\nAdd immediately after `CopyRequest` — identical structure, same JSON tags:\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2 — `api/client.go`: Add `Rename()` method\nAdd immediately after `Copy()` — mirrors it exactly with `/api/rename`:\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    if err := c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil); err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3 — `server/routes.go`: Add `RenameHandler` method\nAdd after `CopyHandler`. Logic flow:\n1. Parse + validate JSON body (400 on missing/invalid)\n2. Validate both names via `model.ParseName()` / `name.IsValid()` → 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n3. Check destination existence via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → 409 if found\n4. Call `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404 if src not found, 500 on other errors\n5. Call `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)`, `m.Remove()`, `m.RemoveLayers()` → 500 on failure\n6. Return `200 {\"status\": \"success\"}`\n\nAll packages needed (`model`, `manifest`, `errtypes`, `CopyModel`, `os`, `fmt`, `errors`) are **already imported** in `routes.go`.\n\n### Step 4 — `server/routes.go`: Register route in `GenerateRoutes()`\nAdd after `r.POST(\"/api/copy\", s.CopyHandler)`:\n```go\nr.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)\n```\n\n### Step 5 — `cmd/cmd.go`: Add `RenameHandler` function\nAdd after `CopyHandler` — mirrors it with double-quoted output per spec:\n```go\nfunc RenameHandler(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n    client, err := api.ClientFromEnvironment()\n    if err != nil { return err }\n    req := api.RenameRequest{Source: args[0], Destination: args[1]}\n    if err := client.Rename(cmd.Context(), &req); err != nil { return err }\n    fmt.Printf(\"Renamed \\\"%s\\\" to \\\"%s\\\"\\n\", args[0], args[1])\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Step 6 — `cmd/cmd.go`: Add `renameCmd` + register it\n```go\nrenameCmd := &cobra.Command{\n    Use:     \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\",\n    Short:   \"Rename a model\",\n    Args:    cobra.ExactArgs(2),\n    PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat,\n    RunE:    RenameHandler,\n}\n```\nAdded to `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` after `copyCmd`.\n\n---\n\nThe full detailed plan with exact code snippets and insertion points is saved at `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/sprightly-fluttering-pillow.md`. Ready to implement?",
